   Dribble to Stop Diabetes at NBA Nation
   Taste of Randolph

   Dribble to Sto pDiabetes NBA Nation

   Dribble to Stop Diabetes is a national multimedia campaign developed by
   the National Basketball Association (NBA), the Women’s National
   Basketball Association (WNBA) and the NBA Development League, in
   collaboration with the American Diabetes Association and Sanofi US to
   encourage basketball fans to live an active, healthy lifestyle and
   raise awareness about diabetes prevention, management and the
   potentially serious health complications that can be associated with
   the disease.
   NBA Nation is a mobile basketball theme-park that allows fans from
   across the country to connect with each other through basketball
   competition. A 53-foot customized 18-wheeler transforms into a 20,000
   square-foot basketball playground that features NBA Players/Legends,
   basketball tournaments, interactive games, technology showcases and
   more. The tour launches during NBA Playoffs and travels through major
   U.S. cities from May through July stopping in highly trafficked
   festivals and destination locations. More than one million people
   participate in NBA Nation.
   Dribble To Stop Diabetes will have a 10X10 tented area at each NBA
   Nation stop. If you would like to volunteer at the ADA tent, please
   contact Mary Sullivan at [27]Msullivan@diabetes.org.
   It’s important to know your risk for diabetes and, if you are at risk,
   talk to your doctor and get tested. Visit
   [28]www.dribbletostopdiabetes.com for more information and to take the
   risk assessment.

   Start Date: Saturday, June 15, 2013
   End Date:   Sunday, June 16, 2013

   This event does not require an RSVP. Registered users can request event
   reminders.
